Radiographic screening of asymmetry and postural changes in orthodontic patients. The role of OPM and of the teleradiography in the diagnosis of the asymmetries and of the postural problems of the orthodontic patients, is pointed out from this analysis on the group of 204 patients from mixed dentition to the adult age with different types of malocclusion. The evidence of a significant amount of patients with asymmetries and incorrected posture shows the utility of this radiological screening and gives advises for a therapeutic approach more corrected.